\begin{abstract}

A large dynamic range is required by the Plastic Scintillator Detector (PSD) of DArk Matter Paricle Explorer (DAMPE), and a double-dynode readout has been developed. To verify this design, a prototype detector module has been constructed and tested with cosmic rays and heavy ion beams.
The results match with the estimation and the readout unit could easily cover the required dynamic range.

\end{abstract}


